Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @Fingerling Potatoes{12%ounce} lengthwise. Place in a large #pot with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are
tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain well and return potatoes to pot.

Meanwhile, cut @Broccoli Florets{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve,
peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}; finely chop a few slices until you have 1 1/2 tsp
(2 1/2 tsp for 4 servings).

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet with a drizzle of
@Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels and season generously
all over with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{} in a large #pan over medium-high heat. Add beef and
cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board. (TIP: Cover with foil to keep warm.)
Rinse and wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, in a #small microwave-safe bowl, combine half the @Red Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}
(you'll use more later), @Sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 4 servings), @Water{1/2%teaspoon}
(1 tsp for 4), @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Stir in sliced shallot, then cover with
#plastic wrap. Microwave for ~{1%minute}. Remove plastic wrap and transfer 1 TBSP
pickling liquid (2 TBSP for 4) to a separate #small bowl.

To bowl with pickling liquid, whisk in @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} and
@Olive Oil{2%tablespoon} (4 TBSP for 4). Season dressing with salt and pepper to taste.

Add @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) to pot with drained potatoes.
Place pot over medium-high heat and cook, stirring, until potato skins are crisp and
browned, ~{3-5%minutes}. (For 4, you may need to work in batches.)

Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium heat. Add chopped shallot and
cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Plum Jam{2%unit}, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2%unit}, remaining vinegar,
and @Water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer; cook, stirring
occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat. Stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted. Season
with salt and pepper to taste.

In a #medium bowl, combine @Mixed Greens{2%ounce}, broccoli, pickled shallot
(draining first), and as much dressing as you like.

Thinly slice beef against the grain.

Divide beef, potatoes, and salad between plates. Spoon sauce over beef and serve.

> Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.